  <data name="TipThemeMode" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Follow system, light, or dark. "Follow system" switches automatically with the Windows light/dark setting.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipColorScheme" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The overall color tone of the papers, affecting background and accent colors.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipMarkdownRender" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How Markdown is rendered in notes. "Enhanced" live-styles headings, lists, bold, etc.; "Basic" does light processing only.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipFullscreenTopmostMode" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When another app is fullscreen, choose whether papers and edge capsules temporarily lower their z-order. Avoid is the default; stay on top keeps them above fullscreen content.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipTodoVisualSize" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Adjust the visual size of todo items. Small is 12, medium keeps the current 13, large is 14, and XL is 15.5.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipEnableTodoNoteLinks" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When on, drag a note onto a to-do item to link them, then use the linked-note button on that item to open the note.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipShowLinkedNoteName" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show the linked note's title after a to-do item that has a note attached.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipHideLinkedNotesFromCapsules" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, notes already attached to a to-do item are removed from the capsule list, so the edge capsules do not duplicate that to-do entry point. When disabled, those notes can still collapse like any normal paper.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipRunLinkedScriptCapsulesOnClick" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, the linked-note button on a to-do item runs the linked script capsule on left-click. Right-click still opens it for editing. Off by default to prevent accidental script runs.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipNewTodoButton" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show the "New to-do" button in the paper's top bar.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipNewNoteButton" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show the "New note" button in the paper's top bar.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipExternalOpenButton" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show the "Open externally" button in the top bar, which writes the note to a temporary file and opens it in the default app.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipExternalExtension" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>File extension used when opening a note externally, e.g. .md or .txt.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipCapsuleMode" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When on, a paper can collapse into a small capsule to save screen space. This is the master switch for the other capsule features.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipDeepCapsuleMode" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Collapsed capsules dock to the right screen edge in a vertical stack and slide out on hover. Requires capsule collapse.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipShowDeepCapsuleWhileExpanded" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When on, opening a paper from an edge capsule keeps a highlighted capsule in its slot. When off, that capsule is hidden and the slot is released until the paper returns to capsule form.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipCapsuleCollapseAll" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show a "Collapse" master capsule atop the docked stack; click it to collapse / expand all capsules at once. Requires edge-align.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipMaxTitleLength" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Maximum number of characters allowed in a paper title, which also caps the title length shown on the capsule.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipStartup" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Launch PaperTodo automatically when Windows starts.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsEnableToolTips" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show hover hints</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipEnableToolTips" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, brief hints appear when the pointer rests on buttons or interactive areas. Setting info icons stay available either way.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsEnableAnimations" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Enable animations</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipEnableAnimations" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, actions like completing, adding, or deleting todos will have smooth animations. Disable this to improve performance on low-end devices.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipPersistentPowerShellProcess" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, script capsules using !pf or !powerf reuse one PowerShell process and return immediately. Variables, location, and loaded state may persist. Turning this off ends the persistent process.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipPreferPowerShell7" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, script capsules prefer PowerShell 7 (pwsh.exe) and fall back to Windows PowerShell when unavailable. Use !pwsh or !ps5 to force one.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TipHideScriptRunWindow" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, scripts run hidden in the background. When off, a PowerShell window may be shown. Normal !p / !power always waits and captures error output; !pf / !powerf only submits the script.</value>
  </data>
